Biomass Briquette.title: Biomass Briquette
Biomass Briquette.subtitle: Eco-friendly, compact fuel blocks from biomass and waste materials
Biomass Briquette.description: Briquettes are eco-friendly, compact fuel blocks created from biomass waste, such as sawdust, agricultural residues, and other organic materials. They provide high calorific value, generate low emissions, and are an economical substitute for conventional fossil fuels in heating and industrial applications.
usesdescription: Used as an energy source in industrial boilers and kilns
Replaces coal and wood in rural heating applications
Ideal for power generation through gasifiers
Utilized in food processing industries for steam generation
Promotes clean energy adoption and reduces deforestation
